this morning the South Bay said goodbye to a Northside local, OG Bodyboarder and all around great guy Tim Tindall (@southbaymoments ), if you’ve spent any amount of time on the Pier or in the Northside lot in the last 15 years you’d know Tim always a camera in hand smile on his face. What a great turnout in the South Bay for the International Surf Festival weekend from 6 Man Volleyball to Velzy-Stevens Pier2Pier paddle and all the events in between, i have hundreds of photos and videos to sort through. Looking forward to sharing some of my favorites this week. Special thanks to the @lacolifeguards for keeping all the participants safe and the stoke high.

The Charlie Saikley 6-Man Tourney always brings out the best in Manhattan Beach. Here is the first of a few posts from the weekend on the hot sand of the legendary south side of the Manhattan Beach Pier.
